    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>While doing a similar search, I found an option that may meet your needs:</p>\n<p>SciJava Jupyter Kernel\n<a href=\"https://github.com/scijava/scijava-jupyter-kernel\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/scijava/scijava-jupyter-kernel</a></p>\n<p>I have not actually run Java against this kernel yet, but it's documentation claims to support Java among a number of other scripting languages.</p>\n<p>It is constructed to run ImageJ (&quot;an open source Java image processing program&quot;): <a href=\"https://imagej.net/Scripting#Supported_languages\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://imagej.net/Scripting#Supported_languages</a></p>\n<p>Jupyter Kernels List (reference):\n<a href=\"https://github.com/jupyter/jupyter/wiki/Jupyter-kernels\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/jupyter/jupyter/wiki/Jupyter-kernels</a></p>\n"
